Prince Zeid bin Ra&#8217;ad Zeid al-Hussein calls for an end to hate speech and discrimination as Saturday marks International Human Rights Day. JOHANNESBURG - As the world celebrates International Human Rights Day, the United Nations has urged governments across the globe to stand up for this fundamental right.The UN says the greatest achievement of the global community since the World War II is the construction of an international human rights system based on the universal declaration of human rights.UN commissioner for human rights Zeid Ra ad al-Hussein has spoken out against the rise of hate speech, incitement of violence, hostility and discrimination.He says it is up to society to end this type of behaviour. We don t have to stand by when those who peddle hate drive wedges of hostility between communities, we can build bridges and stand up for the values of decent and passionate societies. 